  "market_context": "Intraday session following a consolidation phase; price had swept a prior 4-hour low, re-entered range, and formed a shallow opposing run. Analyst waited for new candle to confirm continuation lower with small wick and CISD.",
  "key_observation": "A new 15-minute candle opened lower, reached the prior high early (ideal timing), formed a V-shape reversal with SMT divergence, and exhibited a small wick—signaling high-probability expansion lower into existing FVGs.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified consolidation after sweep of prior 4-hour low and failure to reach prior high, concluding price needed a new candle for valid entry.",
    "Step 2: Waited for new 15-minute candle to open lower (bullish sign initially) and then test the prior high early in the candle’s timeframe.",
    "Step 3: Observed V-shape reversal formation off the prior candle’s high, confirmed by SMT divergence and change in state of delivery (CISD).",
    "Step 4: Noted small wick on the expansion candle, supporting further downside movement into fair value gaps (FVGs) within the range.",
    "Step 5: Recognized the pattern as a fractal continuation (Candle 3) rather than reversal, applying same principles used at higher time frames."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade taken short on continuation lower after CISD and small wick confirmation; target toward FVGs and daily open liquidity.",
  "lessons": "Continuation trades are highest probability when they mirror reversal logic: small wick early, CISD, SMT confirmation, and alignment with HTF structure. Never force entries during consolidation—wait for new candle and ideal wick timing.",
